
# Phase 2 - Simulated IAM Activity

## Process

- Generated IAM-related activity using AWS CLI and console actions
- Listed IAM users and roles to simulate identity enumeration
- Verified current identity using `sts get-caller-identity`
- Listed S3 buckets and described EC2 instances to simulate resource discovery
- Assumed the `LabAdminRole` role using AWS STS
- Executed IAM administrative activity that resulted in creation of an additional IAM user

## Result

Produced IAM-related CloudTrail events including enumeration, resource discovery, role assumption, and identity creation activity.

## Insight

IAM activity provides some of the highest-value cloud security signals because it directly affects access and privilege within the AWS environment.

Role assumption and user creation are especially important to monitor because they may represent administrative changes or privilege escalation pathways.
